sources.reference: Pikovski et al., 'Universal decoherence due to gravitational time dilation' (arXiv:1311.1095v2)
Hasegawa et al., 'Decoherence of Atomic Ensembles in Optical Lattice Clocks by Gravity' (arXiv:2107.02405v2)
Bonder et al., 'Can gravity account for the emergence of classicality?' (arXiv:1509.04363v3)
Anastopoulos & Hu, 'Centre of mass decoherence due to time dilation' (arXiv:1507.05828v5)

model.pmodel_time_noise: V=exp(-(ω0*σ_y*T)^2/2) for run-to-run fractional rate noise σ_y

notes: The ensemble model is inhomogeneous dephasing (not dynamical environment-induced decoherence).
The σ_y model is a minimal parametrization of extra time-structure noise (P-model-specific); real experiments may have correlated noise between arms.
